President Joe Biden authorized an immediate U.S. response to the earthquakes in Turkey on February 6th and directed federal agencies to provide assistance. President Biden called President Erdogan to offer U.S. support, and various U.S. officials expressed condolences and engaged with Turkish counterparts. The U.S. government affirmed that humanitarian assistance is available to all Syrians, and efforts are being made to coordinate with UN agencies and partners in Syria. The Biden-Harris Administration also appreciates the global support received and has a list of vetted organizations responding to the crisis.